<br />
(35) + (35) = 70 (for all the dummies out there)    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Alright I would guess a strategy section would be in order.<br />
First things first. Bid about 3. Going first is no big deal although its nice to pull Aragorn out with the Pony. This deck still does well going second, but you do have to double move more.<br />
The point of the deck is to get the archers out- Legolas and Aragorn with his bow. These guys will relentlessly pick off all sorts of minions and combined with a Strength of Spirit these guys can effectively kill most big minions (Cave Trolls, Witch Kings, and your mom,etc...). The Servants are really helpful,ensuring everyones&#39; survival and after using all the really neat Gandalf events, Barliman will retreive them. Basically the fellowship just walks along and the bad mo fuggas kill all the minions. Its as simple as that. :D<br />
The Minions kick @ss! The point, obviously with the Moria is to swarm and provide a massive beatdown. The Armories are the main motor for this, allowing you to add mucho twilight for playing all the weapons and allowing you to lay the smackdown with a slew of Orcs lead by Old Snarley. There&#39;s not much more to say about these guys except when you lay the Cave Troll down you have to exclaim &quot; Dude! You&#39;re getting a Cave Troll!&quot; just like in the Dell commercials.<br />
Alright , that&#39;s it. That&#39;s just it. Its over.<br />
